In his speech at the National Assembly Building in Seoul, President Trump expressed gratitude for the warm welcome he and First Lady Melania Trump received in South Korea. He highlighted the historical alliance between the United States and South Korea, forged during the Korean War, and praised the economic transformation and achievements of the South Korean people. He contrasted this with the oppressive regime in North Korea, describing the dire conditions under which its citizens live. President Trump emphasized the need for all nations to isolate North Korea and to fully implement United Nations Security Council resolutions. He called for an end to North Korea's aggression and development of nuclear weapons, and expressed hope for a brighter future and reunification of the Korean people.